Question 1 (18 pts)

Let’s assume that there exists a 5 GB file. For all below sub-parts, assume that transfer rate is 50 MB/s and seek time is 3 milliseconds. Remember from class, seek time is the time to find the start position of Each block to read the data from. For simplicity, assume that 1GB = 1000 MB, 1 MB = 1000 KB and so on, and the complete file is stored on just one system.

a) (5 pts)

If the file is stored on a simple file system with a block size of 100 KB, how much time does it take to read the complete file?

\[\begin{align}\text{Total Time}&=\text{Total Seek Time}+\text{Transfer Time}\\&=\text{Seek Time/Block}\times\text{Number of Blocks}+\text{Transfer Time}\end{align}\]

\[\begin{align}\text{Transfer Time}&=\frac{5\text{GB}}{50\text{MB}\cdot\text{s}^{-1}}\\&=100\text{s}\end{align}\]

\[\text{Seek Time/Block}=3\cdot10^{-3}\text{s}\]

\[\begin{align}\text{Number of Blocks}&=\frac{5\text{GB}}{100\text{KB}}\\&=5\cdot10^4\end{align}\]

\[\begin{align}\text{Total Time}&=100\text{s}+3\cdot10^{-3}\text{s}\times5\cdot10^4\\&=100\text{s}+150\text{s}\\&=250\text{s}\end{align}\]

The total time is 250s.

b) (5 pts)

If the file is stored on a Hadoop file system with a block size of 100 MB, how much time does it take to read the complete file?

\[\begin{align}\text{Total Time}&=\text{Total Seek Time}+\text{Transfer Time}\\&=\text{Seek Time/Block}\times\text{Number of Blocks}+\text{Transfer Time}\end{align}\]

\[\begin{align}\text{Transfer Time}&=\frac{5\text{GB}}{50\text{MB}\cdot\text{s}^{-1}}\\&=100\text{s}\end{align}\]

\[\text{Seek Time/Block}=3\cdot10^{-3}\text{s}\]

\[\begin{align}\text{Number of Blocks}&=\frac{5\text{GB}}{100\text{MB}}\\&=50\end{align}\]

\[\begin{align}\text{Total Time}&=100\text{s}+3\cdot10^{-3}\text{s}\times50\\&=100\text{s}+0.15\text{s}\\&=100.15\text{s}\end{align}\]

The total time is 100.15s.

c) (5 pts)

What is the percentage gain of time in the second case as compared to the first case?

(250-100.15)/250*100
## [1] 59.94

The percentage gain is 59.94%.

d) (3 pts)

Give reasons and situations where block size in Question 1a is better than block size in Question 1b, and vice versa.

When the file size is very small, the number of blocks would be small, and the total seek time would be very similar between two situations. Also, if there are a lot of small files that need to be processed, in this case, there is no need to use Hadoop file system.

When the file size is very large and there is only a few files, Hadoop file system is better.
